    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How to Check K-Electric Bill Online — Karachi 2026 Guide</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4"><strong>K-Electric</strong> (formerly Karachi Electric Supply Corporation) is the privately-owned electricity utility serving Karachi — Pakistan's largest city with over 16 million population. Unlike other Pakistani DISCOs which are government-owned, K-Electric has been a private company since 2005 and serves roughly <strong>3.4 million consumers</strong> across the Karachi metropolitan area. K-Electric has its own billing system, separate account number format (13 digits instead of 14), and its own online services. This guide walks you through the complete process of checking your K-Electric bill online, downloading a PDF duplicate, and understanding your bill.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: Visit <a href="/k-electric-bill/" class="underline">pakistanbill.online/k-electric-bill/</a>, enter your <strong>13-digit K-Electric account number</strong> (printed on the top-right of any previous bill, labeled "Account No."), and your current month's bill appears instantly. Free, no login, no app required.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is K-Electric and Where Does It Operate?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">K-Electric is the sole electricity supplier for <strong>Karachi</strong> and its adjacent areas. The company is responsible for electricity generation, transmission, and distribution within its franchise area:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Karachi City</strong> — all 18 towns including Saddar, Clifton, Gulshan, Gulistan-e-Johar, North Nazimabad, Korangi, Malir, Lyari</li>
      <li><strong>Adjacent areas</strong> — Bin Qasim, Gadap, Ibrahim Hyderi, Kathore</li>
      <li><strong>Industrial zones</strong> — SITE, Korangi Industrial Area, FB Area, North Karachi Industrial Area</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you live in Karachi, K-Electric is your electricity supplier — there are no other options. The company operates its own billing system, separate from LESCO, IESCO, and other DISCOs.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is K-Electric Account Number?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">K-Electric uses a <strong>13-digit account number</strong> as the primary identifier for each consumer. This is different from other DISCOs (LESCO, IESCO, FESCO, etc.) which use a 14-digit reference number. Make sure you're using the correct format:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>13 digits</strong> — exactly 13, never more or less</li>
      <li>Only numbers — no letters or dashes</li>
      <li>Example: <code class="bg-neutral-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">0123456789012</code></li>
      <li>Labeled <strong>"Account No."</strong> or <strong>"A/C No."</strong> on the bill</li>
      <li>Stays the same every month</li>
      <li>Required to check bill online, pay at banks, register complaints</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your K-Electric Bill Online</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Find your 13-digit K-Electric account number.</strong> Open any previous K-Electric bill. The account number is printed in bold on the <strong>top-right section</strong>, labeled "Account No." or "A/C No.".</li>
      <li><strong>Open the K-Electric bill checker.</strong> Go to <a href="/k-electric-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/k-electric-bill/</a>. The page is mobile-friendly and works on any browser.</li>
      <li><strong>Enter the 13-digit account number.</strong> Type carefully, count the digits. Avoid leading zeros getting cut off when copy-pasting.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Check Bill".</strong> Your current month's K-Electric bill loads in 2–4 seconds.</li>
      <li><strong>Review bill details</strong>: consumer name, address, billing month, units consumed, total amount, due date, any arrears.</li>
      <li><strong>Download PDF</strong> if you want a duplicate copy. The PDF is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all banks and payment retailers in Karachi.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Shows on Your K-Electric Bill?</h2>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// K-Electric Bill — Top Right Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  K-Electric Bill                   │</p>
      <p>│  Consumer: [Your Name]            │</p>
      <p>│  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Account No: 0123456789012</strong> │   │ ← 13-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Tariff: Domestic B-1     │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading Date: 12-June-26 │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Units Consumed: 320 kWh  │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Current Bill: Rs. 13,800 │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ FPA: Rs. 1,250           │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 15,050│   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 28-June-2026   │   │</p>
      <p>│  └──────────────────────────┘   │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]    │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">K-Electric bills include the same standard line items as other DISCOs: Current Bill, FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment), QTR (Quarterly Tariff Adjustment), FC Surcharge, Electricity Duty, TV Fee, Bank Charges, and Arrears. K-Electric bills also include a unique "K-Electric Additional Surcharge" line that covers the company's capacity payments.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to Pay Your K-Electric Bill</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">K-Electric bills can be paid through all standard payment channels in Karachi:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
