      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where is the account number on K-Electric bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The K-Electric account number is printed on the top-right section of your bill, labeled 'Account No.' or 'A/C No.'. It is 13 digits long and contains only numbers — no letters or dashes.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to pay K-Electric bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay K-Electric bill through JazzCash (Utility Bills → Electricity → K-Electric → 13-digit account number), EasyPaisa, bank mobile apps, bank branches (HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, Bank Alfalah), or any 1Bill shop in Karachi.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the K-Electric helpline?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">K-Electric helpline is 118 (from Karachi) or 021-99000000 from mobile. For power outage complaints, call 118. For billing disputes, call 021-99008200. K-Electric also accepts WhatsApp complaints at 0348-0000118.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why is my K-Electric bill higher than other DISCOs?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">K-Electric bills include an 'Additional Surcharge' that covers capacity payments to the company. This adds about Rs. 1-3 per unit compared to other DISCOs. K-Electric also has slightly different tariff slabs. The base tariffs are regulated by NEPRA and are similar nationwide.</div></details>
